content: Welcome to the last lesson of renjuclass in year 2003!
We have learned two 5th moves for D8 opening
but actually there was another 5th move which was the most popular
thousands of games have been played for this variant
before people found new interest in i8 and j7
Can white play any 6th move other than 6-g7?
Today we will investigate this question
hope it is easy for all of us :)
i experimented g7 as  sure win for black
anf from next lesson, GM shuwang and yyfcsd will teach us 6-g7. ok?
if black take g7 seems sure win for black...
lets play a mouse game first :)
yes, j8 is the correct answer
white has some defense here, but all lose
Xespok, civsnail, Fermat, casar, shuwang, yun_shou, bergamot, sosei, leto, fallnavy, nick_hopper, alcore, whte.
this was an advanced level homework
because there's a correct answer  by Volodymyr. You can find it in renjuclass archive, old homeworks
Please note that, the lib file was created by earlier version of Renlib and cannot be read by latest versions of renlib.
You need to open it with Renlib 3.1 and save it. Then you can use latest renlib to read.
3.1 can read old format and save in new format
if 10-top, then this 11 gives black win
white may have lots of defenses but all lost
if 10-bottom, then this 11 gives the win
for details, please check the old homework answer
